sAllowedUser (web has no userId) — always allow; permission check uses null userId\n- Output format: plain text (not MarkdownV2), HTML-escape for safety, code blocks as <pre>\n- /exec not a registered command — maps to executeSystemCommand service directly\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] T1: Create `src/routes/web-command-router.js` — parseCommand + dispatch to handler, return text result\n- [ ] T2: Add /exec support in web-command-router (calls executeSystemCommand directly, returns formatted output)\n- [ ] T3: Modify `src/routes/api-routes.js` — detect slash commands in /api/chat, add GET /api/commands endpoint\n- [ ] T4: Modify `public/js/main.js` — autocomplete dropdown on '/' keydown\n- [ ] T5: Write tests for web-command-router\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
