{"type":"assistant","message":{"content":[{"text":"The api-routes.js looks good. There's one issue: the `/api/commands` endpoint is placed before the SSE events setup. The commands endpoint needs the registry to be loaded, but `getAvailableCommands()` is called at request time, and the registry is populated when the Telegram bot initializes. This should be fine since commands load at startup.\n\nHowever, there's a subtle issue - the GET /api/commands endpoint needs the registry to be populated. If called before the bot initializes, it might return an empty list (minus `/exec`). Let me verify this is acceptable given the architecture (the bot initializes at startup, so by the time any web requests come in, commands should be registered).\n\nNow let me mark tests done and proceed to code review:","type":"text"}],"id":"req_vrtx_011CZHo11mManPKgPrddKdk8","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":2312,"output_tokens":1,"cache_read_input_tokens":83594},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7831a64a-70c3-467a-b2e5-6975a875912b","uuid":"4b81bd82-1272-4404-8923-fb8843a1b5ae"}
