{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FXSukvziJBMHvQWkqzRqis","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\n     2→PROJECT: PrizmClaw\n     3→LANG: nodejs\n     4→MODULE_INDEX:\n     5→- src/bot: bot.prizm\n     6→- src/http: http.prizm\n     7→- src/pipeline-infra: pipeline-infra.prizm\n     8→- src/routes: routes.prizm\n     9→- src/security: security.prizm\n    10→- src/services: services.prizm\n    11→- src/utils: utils.prizm\n    12→- src/adapters: adapters.prizm\n    13→RULES:\n    14→- All HTTP routes use src/routes/api-routes.js as entry point\n    15→- Telegram bot uses Telegraf framework with command handlers in src/bot/commands/\n    16→- Services are registered in src/services/index.js\n    17→- Security checks use security/ guards before command execution\n    18→- Config loaded from src/config.js with environment variable support\n    19→- MUST use messageRouter.processMessage() for all chat messages (Web + Telegram) — do not call executeAiCli directly for chat\n    20→- MUST call sessionBind.ensureReady() before any sync method in async route handlers\n    21→\n    22→UPDATED: 2026-03-22\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7831a64a-70c3-467a-b2e5-6975a875912b","uuid":"c0f2955c-ce21-4033-ba54-c73f5d3d77c2","timestamp":"2026-03-22T08:21:48.518Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/root.prizm","content":"PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\nPROJECT: PrizmClaw\nLANG: nodejs\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- src/bot: bot.prizm\n- src/http: http.prizm\n- src/pipeline-infra: pipeline-infra.prizm\n- src/routes: routes.prizm\n- src/security: security.prizm\n- src/services: services.prizm\n- src/utils: utils.prizm\n- src/adapters: adapters.prizm\nRULES:\n- All HTTP routes use src/routes/api-routes.js as entry point\n- Telegram bot uses Telegraf framework with command handlers in src/bot/commands/\n- Services are registered in src/services/index.js\n- Security checks use security/ guards before command execution\n- Config loaded from src/config.js with environment variable support\n- MUST use messageRouter.processMessage() for all chat messages (Web + Telegram) — do not call executeAiCli directly for chat\n- MUST call sessionBind.ensureReady() before any sync method in async route handlers\n\nUPDATED: 2026-03-22\n","numLines":23,"startLine":1,"totalLines":23}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_011L82Zgup1UtHm6wcKNrtwJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Plan — F-019: Web Chat Command Support\n     2→\n     3→## Key Components\n     4→\n     5→1. **Web Command Router** (`src/routes/web-command-router.js`) — New service that wraps the Telegram command registry for web context\n     6→2. **API Route Extension** (`src/routes/api-routes.js`) — Detect `/` commands in POST /api/chat, route through web command router, return formatted result\n     7→3. **Commands List Endpoint** — GET /api/commands returns available commands for autocomplete\n     8→4. **Frontend Autocomplete** (`public/js/main.js`) — Dropdown on `/` keydown in textarea, command selection autocomplete\n     9→\n    10→## Data Flow\n    11→\n    12→```\n    13→Web chat input /cli list\n    14→  → POST /api/chat {message: '/cli list'}\n    15→  → api-routes.js: message.startsWith('/') → webCommandRouter.handle(message, sessionId)\n    16→  → webCommandRouter: parseCommand(message) → getCommand('cli') → call handler\n    17→  → handler returns string result\n    18→  → format as HTML-safe text → publish SSE + return in JSON reply\n    19→```\n    20→\n    21→## Files to Create/Modify\n    22→\n    23→- CREATE: `src/routes/web-command-router.js` — Web-adapted command dispatcher\n    24→- MODIFY: `src/routes/api-routes.js` — Add command detection to /api/chat + GET /api/commands\n    25→- MODIFY: `public/js/main.js` — Add command autocomplete UI\n    26→- CREATE: `tests/bot/commands/web-command-router.test.js` — Unit tests\n    27→\n    28→## Architecture Notes\n    29→\n    30→- Web command handler context differs from Telegram ctx: no ctx.reply, uses return value\n    31→- Security: web commands skip isAllowedUser (web has no userId) — always allow; permission check uses null userId\n    32→- Output format: plain text (not MarkdownV2), HTML-escape for safety, code blocks as <pre>\n    33→- /exec not a registered command — maps to executeSystemCommand service directly\n    34→\n    35→## Tasks\n    36→\n    37→- [x] T1: Create `src/routes/web-command-router.js` — parseCommand + dispatch to handler, return text result\n    38→- [x] T2: Add /exec support in web-command-router (calls executeSystemCommand directly, returns formatted output)\n    39→- [x] T3: Modify `src/routes/api-routes.js` — detect slash commands in /api/chat, add GET /api/commands endpoint\n    40→- [x] T4: Modify `public/js/main.js` — autocomplete dropdown on '/' keydown\n    41→- [x] T5: Write tests for web-command-router\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7831a64a-70c3-467a-b2e5-6975a875912b","uuid":"19f629a2-5b7c-4af8-8236-544911f8825f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T08:21:48.520Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/019-web-chat-command-support/plan.md","content":"# Plan — F-019: Web Chat Command Support\n\n## Key Components\n\n1. **Web Command Router** (`src/routes/web-command-router.js`) — New service that wraps the Telegram command registry for web context\n2. **API Route Extension** (`src/routes/api-routes.js`) — Detect `/` commands in POST /api/chat, route through web command router, return formatted result\n3. **Commands List Endpoint** — GET /api/commands returns available commands for autocomplete\n4. **Frontend Autocomplete** (`public/js/main.js`) — Dropdown on `/` keydown in textarea, command selection autocomplete\n\n## Data Flow\n\n```\nWeb chat input /cli list\n  → POST /api/chat {message: '/cli list'}\n  → api-routes.js: message.startsWith('/') → webCommandRouter.handle(message, sessionId)\n  → webCommandRouter: parseCommand(message) → getCommand('cli') → call handler\n  → handler returns string result\n  → format as HTML-safe text → publish SSE + return in JSON reply\n```\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n- CREATE: `src/routes/web-command-router.js` — Web-adapted command dispatcher\n- MODIFY: `src/routes/api-routes.js` — Add command detection to /api/chat + GET /api/commands\n- MODIFY: `public/js/main.js` — Add command autocomplete UI\n- CREATE: `tests/bot/commands/web-command-router.test.js` — Unit tests\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n- Web command handler context differs from Telegram ctx: no ctx.reply, uses return value\n- Security: web commands skip isAllowedUser (web has no userId) — always allow; permission check uses null userId\n- Output format: plain text (not MarkdownV2), HTML-escape for safety, code blocks as <pre>\n- /exec not a registered command — maps to executeSystemCommand service directly\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [x] T1: Create `src/routes/web-command-router.js` — parseCommand + dispatch to handler, return text result\n- [x] T2: Add /exec support in web-command-router (calls executeSystemCommand directly, returns formatted output)\n- [x] T3: Modify `src/routes/api-routes.js` — detect slash commands in /api/chat, add GET /api/commands endpoint\n- [x] T4: Modify `public/js/main.js` — autocomplete dropdown on '/' keydown\n- [x] T5: Write tests for web-command-router\n","numLines":42,"startLine":1,"totalLines":42}}}
