orts, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7831a64a-70c3-467a-b2e5-6975a875912b","uuid":"43b2db7e-6a3c-49d6-a08e-b94a84c011a1","timestamp":"2026-03-22T08:22:41.890Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/security/permission-guard.js","content":"    return configuredRole;\n  }\n\n  // Default to admin for unknown users (open-by-default mode)\n  return 'admin';\n}\n\n/**\n * Check if user is admin\n * @param {string|number} userId\n * @returns {boolean}\n */\nexport function isAdmin(userId) {\n  return getUserRole(userId) === 'admin';\n}\n\n/**\n * Check if user can execute command\n * @param {string|number} userId\n * @param {string} command - Command name\n * @returns {{ allowed: boolean, requiresConfirmation: boolean, reason?: string }}\n */\nexport function checkCommandPermission(userId, command) {\n  const userRole = getUserRole(userId);\n  const minRole = COMMAND_MIN_ROLE[command] || 'viewer';\n\n  // Check role hierarchy\n  const userLevel = ROLE_HIERARCHY[userRole];\n  const requiredLevel = ROLE_HIERARCHY[minRole];\n\n  if (userLevel < requiredLevel) {\n    return {\n      allowed: false,\n      requiresConfirmation: false,\n      reason: `权限不足。此命令需要 ${minRole} 权限，当前权限: ${userRole}。`\n    };\n  }\n\n  // Check if this is a high-risk command requiring confirmation\n  const requiresConfirmation = HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS.has(command);\n\n  return {\n    allowed: true,\n    requiresConfirmation\n  };\n}\n\nexport default {\n  getUserRole,\n  checkCommandPermission,","numLines":50,"startLine":100,"totalLines":155}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"content":[{"text":"I now have all the information needed for the review. This is a critical finding — `getUserRole(null)` returns `'admin'` (line 103: \"Default to admin for unknown users (open-by-default mode)\"), which means web users get `admin` role, but the router bypasses `checkCommandPermission` entirely anyway.\n\n---\n\n## Code Review Report — F-019: Web Chat Command Support\n\n**Feature**: Web Chat Command Support  \n**Review Iteration**: 1/5  \n**Files Reviewed**: `src/routes/web-command-router.js`, `src/routes/api-routes.js`, `public/js/main.js`, `tests/bot/commands/web-command-router.test.js`\n\n---\n\n### Findings\n\n---\n\n#### [HIGH] Permission system bypassed for web commands\n\n- **File**: `src/routes/web-command-router.js:110–138`\n- **Dimension**: security\n- **Description**: The web handler context hardcodes `userRole: 'operator'` and `requiresConfirmation: false`, bypassing `checkCommandPermission()` entirely. Commands like `kill` (requires admin), `sessions` (requires admin), `stop` (requires admin), `config` (requires admin) will execute for any web user. The Telegram path always calls `checkCommandPermission(userId, commandName)` before dispatching — the web path has no equivalent gate. Note: per `permission-guard.js:103`, `getUserRole(null)` returns `'admin'` (open-by-default), so passing `userId: null` through the check would actually grant access — but the plan explicitly says to skip auth for web, so this is an intentional design decision. Please confirm: is bypassing command-level permission checks for web users intentional for this project's threat model?\n- **Suggestion**: If intentional, add a comment to `webHandlerCtx` noting \"web channel — permission checks intentionally skipped (open-by-default design)\". If not intentional, add `checkCommandPermission(null, parsed.command)` before dispatch, which will pass for all commands given the open-by-default behavior.\n\n---\n\n#### [HIGH] XSS via `cmd.description` in autocomplete dropdown\n\n- **File**: `public/js/main.js:156`\n- **Dimension**: security\n- **Description**: The dropdown item uses `item.innerHTML = \\`<strong>/${cmd.name}</strong> — ${cmd.description}\\``. The `cmd.description` comes from the server response (`/api/commands`) which contains command descriptions from the registry. Currently all descriptions are hardcoded strings, but if a description ever contains `<`, `>`, or `&` characters (e.g. a command described as \"Show <key>=value pairs\"), this is an XSS vector. `cmd.name` has the same issue.\n- **Suggestion**: Use `textContent` for the description part, or escape both `cmd.name` and `cmd.description` before interpolating into innerHTML:\n  ```js\n  const strong = document.createElement('strong');\n  strong.textContent = `/${cmd.name}`;\n  item.append(strong, ` — ${cmd.description}`);\n  ```\n\n---\n\n#### [MEDIUM] Double message display when command result arrives via both HTTP and SSE\n\n- **File**: `src/routes/api-routes.js:134–143` + `public/js/main.js:240–248`\n- **Dimension**: spec-compliance / code quality\n- **Description**: When a web command runs, `api-routes.js` publishes the result to `realtimeHub` (triggering `assistant_done` SSE event) AND returns the result in the HTTP response. The frontend handles the HTTP response in the `callJson()` result (line 340–342) AND the SSE `assistant_done` event (line 244–247). Both paths call `appendMessage()`. The SSE handler's guard `else if (payload.isCommand)` should prevent the duplicate when `streamingMessageBody` is null — but `streamingMessageBody` is reset to null at line 329 before the request, and the HTTP response arrives before SSE. So: HTTP response appends the message (line 342), then the SSE event arrives with `isCommand: true` and `streamingMessageBody === null`, triggering a second `appendMessage` call (line 246). Result: command output appears twice.\n- **Suggestion**: Track that a command response was already displayed. Either: (a) don't publish to `realtimeHub` for synchronous web commands (remove lines 138–141 in api-routes.js), since the HTTP response is sufficient; or (b) set a flag (e.g. `state.lastCommandDisplayed = true`) in the HTTP handler and check it in the SSE handler.\n\n---\n\n#### [MEDIUM] `ac5` — Loading state not shown for commands (partial AC5 compliance)\n\n- **File**: `public/js/main.js:333`\n- **Dimension**: spec-compliance\n- **Description**: AC5 requires \"命令执行过程中显示加载状态\". The chat form submit sets `setBusy(true, '聊天处理中...')` which covers the loading state generically. However, commands that take time (e.g. `/exec sleep 5`) will show the generic \"聊天处理中...\" rather than a command-specific loading indicator. The spec says \"long output supports segmented display\" — the current implementation collects all output then returns it at once. AC5 is partially met (loading indicator via setBusy) but the \"分段展示\" (segmented display) aspect is not implemented.\n- **Suggestion**: For the loading state, consider changing the status text to \"命令执行中...\" when a slash command is detected before sending. For segmented display, this would require streaming command output which is a larger change — acceptable to defer with a note.\n\n---\n\n#### [MEDIUM] `routeWebCommand` returns `null` for `parseCommand` failure on slash-only input\n\n- **File**: `src/routes/web-command-router.js:90–92`\n- **Dimension**: code quality\n- **Description**: If `parseCommand` returns `null` (e.g. for input `/` or `/ `), `routeWebCommand` returns `null`, which causes the api-routes.js handler to fall through to `messageRouter.processMessage()`. A message of just `/` will then be sent to the AI as a chat message rather than showing an \"invalid command\" error. This is likely not the desired UX.\n- **Suggestion**: After the `parseCommand(text, aliasMap)` null check, add: `if (text.trim() === '/' || !parsed) { return escapeHtml('请输入命令。输入 / 查看可用命令。'); }`\n\n---\n\n#### [MEDIUM] Autocomplete shows all commands when user types exactly `/`\n\n- **File**: `public/js/main.js:177–181`\n- **Dimension**: spec-compliance (AC4)\n- **Description**: AC4 requires \"输入 / 时展示可用命令列表\". When `filterCommands('/')` is called with query `''` (empty string after removing `/`), `cmd.name.startsWith('')` returns `true` for every command. This is correct behavior (show all commands), but there are ~30+ registered commands, which may cause an overwhelming list. The implementation does technically satisfy AC4.\n\n---\n\n#### [LOW] Dead variable `repliedText` in test\n\n- **File**: `tests/bot/commands/web-command-router.test.js:31`\n- **Dimension**: code quality\n- **Description**: `let repliedText = ''` is declared but never used in the \"dispatches to registered command handler\" test.\n- **Suggestion**: Remove the unused variable.\n\n---\n\n#### [LOW] `args` weaker assertion in test\n\n- **File**: `tests/bot/commands/web-command-router.test.js:72`\n- **Dimension**: test coverage\n- **Description**: `assert.ok(receivedArgs.length > 0 || true)` — the `|| true` makes this assertion always pass regardless of args. The test provides no actual coverage for argument passing.\n- **Suggestion**: Remove `|| true` and assert `receivedArgs.length > 0`.\n\n---\n\n#### [LOW] `executeSystemCommand` import unused after F-019\n\n- **File**: `src/routes/api-routes.js:4`\n- **Dimension**: code quality\n- **Description**: `executeSystemCommand` is still imported at line 4 (pre-existing, used by `POST /api/system/exec`). The new `web-command-router.js` also imports it. No duplication issue, just noting both use the same service correctly.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|----------|-------|\n| CRITICAL | 0 |\n| HIGH | 2 |\n| MEDIUM | 4 |\n| LOW | 3 |\n\n### Verdict: **PASS WITH WARNINGS**\n\nNo CRITICAL findings. Two HIGH findings:\n1. **Permission bypass** — likely intentional given open-by-default design, but needs explicit confirmation or comment\n2. **XSS in autocomplete dropdown** — `innerHTML` with unescaped server data, must fix before ship\n\n**Priority fixes before commit**:\n- Fix the XSS in the dropdown (HIGH, trivial to fix)\n- Confirm/document the permission bypass (HIGH, or add a comment)\n- Fix the double-display bug (MEDIUM, straightforward)\n\n**Handoff**: Address HIGH findings, then `/prizmkit-retrospective`","type":"text"}],"id":"req_vrtx_011CZHo8FZmAdJjs1eRkyDvT","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":111904,"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7831a64a-70c3-467a-b2e5-6975a875912b","uuid":"496de029-ac99-41e0-a75b-9604194fb4f9"}
